<h2 id="section-top">Sleep Medicine</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=27">Barking, Havering and Redbridge University Hospitals NHS Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent1b8efb4ebb09445d897dd33ac66405e6">
</div>
<p>We provide information, advice and education on obstructive sleep apnoea including:</p>
<p>    * Respiratory polysomnography (sleep study)sleep apnoea<br/>    * Blood gas analysis<br/>    * Treatment (domiciliary CPAP )</p>
<p>We have a helpline for advice open Monday to Friday 8am to 4pm 0208 970 8332.</p>
<p>We are based in the Chest Clinic at King George Hospital, open 8am to 4pm Monday to Friday.</p>
<p>Lesley Holland is our Sleep Apnoea Nurse Specialist and can be contacted on 0208 970 8332.<br/>Dr R Banka is our Clinical Lead and Respiratory Consultant<br/>Mr B Kotecha is our ENT Consultant<br/>Martine Watts and Carole Hodder are our respiratory physiologists</p>
<p>We have strong links with ENT services for simple snorers and with dieticians and local obesity clinics.</p>
<p>We can provide patients with written information leaflets including information on the use and care of equipment, advice from DVLA, British Lung Foundation and the British Snoring and Sleep Association.</p>
<p>"You are a woman of your word as it sure did change my life thank you"<br/>Terry Smith Feb 2012<br/> <br/>"I’d forgotten how good life could be"<br/>Belinda Gibson Nov 2011</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
